:"Remove the cover and take a look at the drive gear.";i:20;s:52:"It is white nylon and is just in front of the motor.";i:21;s:79:"You will find it stripped and what looks like white sawdust all over the place.";i:22;s:58:"The part number is 41A2817 and it comes with instructions.";i:23;s:14:"Answer 1 of 3.";i:24;s:49:"1 Check to make sure the opener is getting power.";i:25;s:53:"Simply push the button and see if the light comes on.";i:26;s:94:"If the light does not come on then check the power by plugging a light or fan into the socket.";i:27;s:59:"Maybe it is as simple as a GFI or circuit breaker flipping.";i:28;s:20:"However if you hear.";i:29;s:140:"If the shoe is latched into the trolley and the trolley is moving with the belt or chain then look at the door bracket C and the two arms D.";i:30;s:44:"The motor should be driving a chain or belt.";i:31;s:108:"If the chain or belt moves then the opener motor is OK and the problem is probably at the emergency release.";i:32;s:56:"The door may not be connected to the garage door opener.";i:33;s:103:"Depending on your opener you may see only the trolley move along the rail when you activate the opener.";i:34;s:55:"Ensure the door is connected to the garage door opener.";i:35;s:55:"Use the emergency release handle to reconnect the door.";i:36;s:56:"The trolley is on garage door end not on the opener end.";i:37;s:142:"I disconnected the chain and pressed the wall switch to make sure the gear rotated clockwise so that it would be as if garage door was closed.";i:38;s:136:"With the garage door still disengaged I connected the chain back and pressed the button on the wall to see if the trolley would reverse.";i:39;s:59:"Get shopping advice from experts friends and the community.";i:40;s:56:"My Craftsman garage door motor is not turning the chain.";i:41;s:106:"I do not see the sprocket on top turning either though the motor is running through the up and down cycle.";i:42;s:48:"I have not removed the casing yet to look at it.";i:43;s:79:"I have been manually operating the door for some time probably for over a year.";i:44;s:65:"12 hp Craftsman garage door openermotor runs chain does not move.";i:45;s:86:"Already checked chain is on the gear - Answered by a verified Home Improvement Expert.";i:46;s:93:"My garage door opener LiftMaster 13 HP stops partially through the cycle of closing the door.";i:47;s:95:"I have removed the chain from the gear attached to the sprocket and tried cycling it like that.";i:48;s:56:"I wanted to see how it performed with no weight to lift.";i:49;s:82:"Even with no chain attached the thing stops before it gets to the bottom position.";i:50;s:145:"If the chain has come off you will need to loosen the chain tension place the chain back over the sprocket and tighten it to the correct tension.";i:51;s:141:"Your user manual should have details on how to perform this but usually there is a screw you adjust on the trolley that controls the tension.";i:52;s:57:"Check that nothing has fallen into the garage door track.";i:53;s:51:"If it has remove it and try opening the door again.";i:54;s:59:"This may have been what was stopping the door from opening.";i:55;s:40:"Take a look at your garage door springs.";i:56;s:65:"These are what gives your garage door the tension needed to open.";i:57;s:58:"If theyve broken then that will be why the door wont open.";i:58;s:59:"Detach the opener by pulling the emergency handle downward.";i:59;s:62:"The next step is to attempt to open your garage door manually.";i:60;s:79:"This will determine if the issue is connected to the door itself or the opener.";i:61;s:71:"If you are able to raise your garage door easily it is not the problem.";i:62;s:69:"This indicates that something in the opener system has malfunctioned.";i:63;s:119:"Do not hesitate to contact an 365 Overhead Door Gate at 214 980-2015 to quickly and easily fix your garage door system.";i:64;s:80:"Garage doors are under a tremendous amount of tension and can be very dangerous.